  "prompt": "What percentage of freshers are accepted into the IIM's every year?",
  "response": "The percentage of freshers accepted into the Indian Institutes of Management (IIMs) varies each year based on factors such as the number of applicants, the number of available seats, and admission policies. Generally, IIMs are highly competitive, with acceptance rates often ranging from 1% to 5%.\n\nTo provide a clearer picture, in a typical admission cycle for the flagship two-year MBA program, several thousand candidates apply, but only a few hundred are admitted across all IIMs. Freshers, or candidates with no prior work experience, may constitute a smaller portion of the accepted candidates compared to those with work experience.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date statistics, it is advisable to refer to specific IIM websites or their official admission reports.",
